  "text": "Specific aspects contributing to complications in salvage surgery include advanced medical co-morbidities, comorbidities related to prior treatment for HNSCC and prior tracheostomy, age and tumor location outside the larynx [CITATION_1] . recurrent tumors of the oropharynx, hypopharynx and larynx are diagnosed in more advanced disease stages compared with primary tumors [CITATION_2] . therefore, a wellexperienced surgical team must conduct salvage surgery. An interdisciplinary approach to minimize complications and improve survival and functional outcome is required.",
